  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      TIPIC syndrome (previously called carotidynia) is a rare entity of unknown cause, where the&#xD;
      patient has a temporary cervical pain associated with a suggestive inflammation around the&#xD;
      carotid artery. Usually considered as a unique and benign episode, some patients have&#xD;
      recurrences and the follow-up is usually short. In this study the investigators aim to&#xD;
      evaluate patients who presented a TIPIC episode at least 3 months before, clinically and with&#xD;
      a cervical doppler ultrasound&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
